ehensive science of humanity which recognizes the value of memory and imagination.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aEducationxPhilosophy. 0aEducation, Higher. 4aEducation & History Of Education. 4aHistory. 4aPhilosophy.  a18th century Italian philosopher.  aAesthetics.  aAnalytic philosophy.  aAncient.  aClassroom Management.  aContemporary.  aCritical Thinking.  aCurriculum.  aEastern philosophy.  aEducation Theory.  aEducation and Culture.  aEducation.  aEducational Leadership.  aEducational Philosophy.  aEducational Policy.  aEducational Research.  aEducational Systems.  aEmpiricist.  aEpistemology.  aGiambattista Vico.  aIndividual Philosopher.  aIndividual Philosophers.  aItalian philosopher.  aeducation majors.  aeducation masters.  ahistory of education.  ahistory of philosophy of education.  ahistory of philosophy.  ahistory of rhetoric.  ahumanistic education.  ahumanistic tradition.  aintellectual history.  aliterary theory.  amodern philosophy.  aphilosophy of education.  aphilosophy of rhetoric.  aphilosophy.  arhetoric.  ascience of humanity.  ascientism-versus-humanism debat.1 aGianturco, Elio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVerene, Donald Phillip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150173259140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501732591423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501732591/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles